      • params

        public final LinkedHashMap<String,Vector<String>> params
        Parsed, percent decoded parameters from URI and, in case of a POST request body using , data. The keys are the parameter names. Each value is an ordered collection of Strings containing the bindings for the named parameter. The order of the URL parameters is preserved by the LinkedHashMap. The order of the bindings for each parameter is preserved by the Vector.

    • Method Detail

        public InputStream getInputStream()
        The input stream. A request body will have already been decoded into params. Otherwise, this argument may be used to read the request body. The input stream will be closed regardless by the caller.
